    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, crumble in the <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong> using your hands<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the ravioli for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>spinach & ricotta ravioli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mushrooms are beginning to soften, add the <strong>cracked black pepper</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min further</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>soft cheese </strong>to the mushrooms and cook for 1 min or until the cheese has melted</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> of the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water </strong>to the sauce and give everything a good mix up</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the pan from the heat and stir in<strong> </strong>most of the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save some for garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>cacio e pepe sauce</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>to the pan and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/truffle-cacio-e-pepe-sauce-with-spinach-and-ricotta-ravioli/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>cacio e pepe sauce with spinach & ricotta ravioli </strong>and drizzle over the <strong>truffle oil</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
